-- Anthony Scores 40 Points as Knicks Give Magic 8th Straight Loss
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-01-06T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-06/anthony-scores-40-points-as-knicks-give-magic-8th-straight-loss.html
Carmelo Anthony  scored 40 points as
the New York Knicks handed the Orlando Magic their eighth
straight loss with a 114-106 National Basketball Association
victory.  The Knicks (23-10) top the Eastern Conferenceâ€™s five-team
Atlantic Division, 4 1/2 games ahead of the Brooklyn Nets
(19-15) who defeated the Sacramento Kings 113-93 last night.  The Knicks had a 59-55 advantage at halftime and then
trailed 89-81 at the end of the third quarter. They outscored
the Magic 33-17 in the final period at Amway Center in Orlando.  J.R. Smith came off the bench to score 18 points for the
Knicks,  Jason Kidd  added 15 points and Tyson Chandler had 14
points and 12 rebounds.  Jameer Nelson  and Arron Afflalo each had 29 points for the
Magic (12-21), who had 14 turnovers that the Knicks converted
into 23 points.  The Magic are in fourth place in the five team Southeast
Division, 14 1/2 points behind the Miami Heat (22-9).  To contact the reporter on this story:
